It's Mother's Day Mother's Day celebrated honouring mothers and motherhood, maternal bonds and the influence of mothers in society. Cameroon's Dang re-elected Cameroon's Roger Nkodo Dang re-elected president of the Pan African Parliament after garnering 133 of the 224 votes cast. Nigeria pharmaceuticals' reprieve Authorities re-open three pharmaceutical companies shut down for producing cough syrup containing forbidden codeine in Nigeria. Emzor Pharmaceuticals, Peace Standard Pharmaceutical and Bioraj Pharmaceutical were shut down on May 7. Gor meet Hull City Kenya's Premier League soccer champions Gor Mahia play English Championship club Hall City in a friendly match at the Safaricom Stadium, Kasarani in Nairobi.   Call to prosecute South Sudanese leaders President pays tribute to the self-taught veteran photographer Sam Nzima